<div id="review_3435169162" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3435169162" />
    <a title="Kelly_Hunsaker_reads ..." class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1330063-kelly-hunsaker-reads"><img alt="Kelly_Hunsaker_reads ..." src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1217387294p2/1330063.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3435169162?book_show_action=true">Jul 10, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelly_Hunsaker_reads ..." class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelly_Hunsaker_reads ..." href="/user/show/1330063-kelly-hunsaker-reads">Kelly_Hunsaker_reads ...</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1330063-kelly-hunsaker-reads?shelf=american-lit">american-lit</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1330063-kelly-hunsaker-reads?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1330063-kelly-hunsaker-reads?shelf=read-in-2020">read-in-2020</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1330063-kelly-hunsaker-reads?shelf=coming-of-age">coming-of-age</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1330063-kelly-hunsaker-reads?shelf=oprah-bookclub">oprah-bookclub</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3435169162" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3037355160075190230">I enjoyed this book about a quirky, unique and odd little girl who suffers from Tourette&apos;s Syndrome in the 1950s before anyone understood what it was. That is, until the last 25 pages. Up until that point I would give the book 4 stars. But the ending felt force and rushed, and the religiosity felt judgmental and negative. I hated it. I live near a religious &quot;college&quot; that teaches faith healing. They actually believe that they can heal anyone of anything through prayer, and will grab hold of me w</span>
  <span id="freeText3037355160075190230" style="display:none">I enjoyed this book about a quirky, unique and odd little girl who suffers from Tourette's Syndrome in the 1950s before anyone understood what it was. That is, until the last 25 pages. Up until that point I would give the book 4 stars. But the ending felt force and rushed, and the religiosity felt judgmental and negative. I hated it. I live near a religious "college" that teaches faith healing. They actually believe that they can heal anyone of anything through prayer, and will grab hold of me when they see me in public and pray on me without asking whether I want to be touched or prayed for. It is an arrogant view of prayer: "I am holier than you and my prayers have more weight than yours." This is what the ending of the book felt like. Ugh. That ending spoiled the entire book for me. I was no longer charmed. I just felt manipulated.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="3037355160075190230" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


